The paper deals with spoken question answering, which involves natural language processing and speech recognition. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of adversarial models suggests a focus on deep learning, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
